Sincerely,

The Freeman Leadership Team

post_text:
Dear Freeman Students, Staff, and Parents,

Due to the air quality conditions, Freeman SD will provide classes 100% virtually for all K-12 students on Monday, September 14, 2020. There will be no pre-school.

Freeman Staff will work from campus, we will continue to monitor the situation, and we will communicate any changes.

Sincerely,

The Freeman Leadership Team

post_text:
Freeman Families: hopefully by now you have scheduled your Meet & Greet with your students' teacher(s). If not, please log in to Skyward Family Access and get that taken care of in Conference Scheduler ASAP. This will give your student(s) the opportunity to meet their teacher or advisor, checkout a chromebook (if needed), checkout textbooks and learn more about their virtual learning plan.

FHS Parents Only: there will be an informational Zoom meeting tonight at 7pm to provide insight into our virtual learning plan for high school students. In this zoom, we will cover:
* Individual student/teacher meetings
* Chromebook distribution
* Schedule change process
* Daily schedule for teaching and learning
* How to have attendance count - what to do if your student cannot log in during instruction
* Credits and college and career planning
* Athletics update

Check your email for the Zoom link. It will be recorded for later viewing if you are unable to attend.

Tomorrow is yearbook distribution for high school students who purchased a yearbook. Come by the high school between 10am-12:30pm. Only the student or parent who purchased the yearbook will be able to grab it - no getting them for friends, sorry. Then, students are welcome to head over to the Golden Gem for ice cream sandwiches and a chance to sign yearbooks outdoors while social distancing (we encourage them to wear masks).

If this time does not work for you please email Mrs. Bailey (rbailey@freemansd.org) about arranging a time to pick it up in August or when we return in the Fall.

post_text: Friday Night Lights for the Scotties! Tomorrow, 4/10 at 8:20pm (20:20 military time) Mrs. Bailey and Mr. Herda will be lighting up the Football Field in honor of our class of 2020 and the 2020 spring sports teams that lost their season due to the school closures. post_text: Our very own Ken Spiering! We are so blessed to have him at Freeman.
shared_text:
STCU
November 25, 2019 at 1:00 PM ¬∑

200,000 members, 200,000 stories.
This week we're sharing a few of their stories and showing our gratitude to all our members.

Ken Spiering, artist and educator:

Ken's work transformed Spokane: from the majestic Redband trout sculptures at the Convention Center and leaping cougars at the STA Plaza to his iconic "Childhood Express" - a.k.a the Big Red Wagon at Riverfront Park - chances are that you're already familiar with his artistic side.

Ken taught art for 30 years at area colleges, and is finishing out his teaching career as a part-time art teacher at Freeman School District 358.

Read more of Ken's story here: http://bit.ly/2KU5ZER
Photo by Zack Berlat, courtesy of Gonzaga University

post_text:
Are you aware that every year we have students that are in need of financial assistance in order to be able to participate in clubs and sports, take AP and SAT exams, purchase basic school supplies and much more?

You can help! Every year InvestED provides direct and immediate funding to students in need. Last year they helped over 25,000 students at over 600 schools and this year they want to double that amount. At Freeman we were able to help 24 students with just over $1000 in school-related expenses. Your donation will go directly into the InvestED Fund at Freeman High School School to help the students in need here. Simply designate your donation to Freeman High School from the drop down list on the donation page, and don't forget to share this campaign on your social pages!

For a limited time, every donation to Freeman will be matched - up to $500 so if you are planning any end of year giving, please consider this opportunity.

Please follow the link below to go to our donation page.

post_text: Congratulations to Kobe T. who went to Seattle a week ago to receive his 1st place award from the Holocaust Center for Humanity's writing/art/video contest. Over 60 schools participated in this year's contest. He was able to meet Peter Metzelaar, the subject of his video project (Peter spoke to our students 5 years ago). For first place, Kobe's video will be featured on the Holocaust Center's website, and he also won $200.

post_text: The Freeman FFA Trap Team is your 2019 State Champions. They competed in the two day Washington State FFA State Invitational trapshoot and came home with 15 trophies. There were 202 competitors with 42 Teams. Freeman 1 shot a 366/400 to win the State Title for the 3rd time in 4 years. Team 1 roster: Tyler F. Wyatt S. Tyson D. Paysen P, and William F. Freeman 2 took 4th for the 3rd year in a row with a 345/400. Team 2 roster: Triston C. Nolan D. Jaron I. Reagan S. Garret B. Freeman 3 took 8th place with a 321. Freeman 3 roster: Ryan F. Hailee C. Zac G. Kate D. Josh W. They also took an alternate squad which had Daisy F. and Ethan F. who also shot very well for their first state competition. The Freeman Trap Team has brought home 9 top 5 team trophies at the state shoot in the last 6 years. Including 3) STATE CHAMPIONSHIPS, 2) 2nd place trophies, 1) 3rd place trophy, and 3) 4th place trophies. CONGRATULATIONS!

HIGH SCHOOL SPRING SPORTS BEGIN MONDAY, FEB. 25TH!

Due to Mother Nature not cooperating, Track, Tennis, Baseball, and Softball will all start practice next Monday here at the High School on an indoor rotation after school. Golf will start practice the following Monday on March 4th with the location to be determined.

Our schedules have been set and can be found on the website by following this link: https://www.freemansd.org/domain/206

Please keep in mind that there will be a lot of factors moving forward but we hope to keep the schedules as close to the same as possible and avoid rescheduling and cancellations.

Finally, please make sure you have all the paperwork completed, physical turned in, and sports fees paid for your student-athlete so they can start practice right away and be ready to go for the first contests.

If you have any questions, please feel free to contact me at any time. Thank you and Go Scotties!

Kris Herda, Athletic Director
kherda@freemansd.org
